{
  "stem": "12289.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It-- it was a disgrace, a dishonor that-- that in modern times, you-- you'd disqualify a whole race like that, that they are not worthy of being a member of society and along and all that.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And all these regulations, that the Jews, the Jewish people were not allowed to sit on the-- on the-- on the chairs and everything in the-- in the parks.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They were not allowed to travel by train.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They were not allowed.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They would had to live in-- in certain houses.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "All this just came like-- upon us, like that.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, more or less.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They-- they-- they operated quickly, like that, you see, the Germans.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then-- then the question was, what can we do now?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They were queuing up, outside our embassy and outside the Swiss and outside the other neutral embassies, pleading for help.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And that-- what could we do?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Well-- very hard.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "There was nothing in our book of instructions, who told us what-- how we could save people of other nationalities.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We-- we are representing Sweden.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We are-- are helping Swedish citizens and all that, with the working for the relationship between Sweden and that country where we are staying and all that.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But to take a whole group of-- of other nationals under our protection, and-- and how could we do that?",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But that's the-- the time when I came to think of, the only way we can do this is to give-- and we got the authorisation from Sweden--",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They have-- there were so many relatives, Jewish relatives in Stockholm and all that, who were pressing the-- pushing the Foreign Office to do something and all that.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So we suggested that those who have relations with Sweden, relatives or commercial relations, we could give them a visa to Sweden.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
